derision
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:sleety bad weather; drizzle. Compare murk.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (Wellington trampers') ca1940 R. Mason Taraura Tramping Club, Wellington Usually stronger than `muck': hail, heavy cold rain, wind-driven rain generally holds some idea that human beings are at the mercy of the elements.
